# Tailwind CSS Rules

- Use design tokens from `src/new-ui/tokens/` instead of hardcoded values
- Prefer semantic color classes over arbitrary values
- Use `tw-` prefix for all Tailwind classes to avoid conflicts
- Group related classes logically (layout, spacing, colors, etc.)
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes

## Design Token Usage

```tsx
// ✅ Good - using design tokens
<div className="tw-bg-background-primary tw-text-foreground-primary tw-p-lg tw-rounded-md">

// ❌ Bad - hardcoded values
<div className="tw-bg-white tw-text-black tw-p-4 tw-rounded-lg">
```

## Class Organization

```tsx
// ✅ Good - logical grouping
<button className={cn(
  // Layout
  "tw-flex tw-items-center tw-justify-center",
  // Spacing
  "tw-px-lg tw-py-md tw-gap-sm",
  // Colors
  "tw-bg-primary tw-text-primary-foreground",
  // States
  "hover:tw-bg-primary/90 focus:tw-ring-2 focus:tw-ring-primary",
  // Typography
  "tw-text-sm tw-font-medium",
  // Borders
  "tw-border tw-border-border tw-rounded-md",
  // Transitions
  "tw-transition-colors",
  // Conditional
  disabled && "tw-opacity-50 tw-cursor-not-allowed"
)}>
```

## Responsive Design

```tsx
// ✅ Good - mobile-first approach
<div className="tw-grid tw-grid-cols-1 md:tw-grid-cols-2 lg:tw-grid-cols-3 tw-gap-lg">

// ❌ Bad - desktop-first
<div className="tw-grid tw-grid-cols-3 lg:tw-grid-cols-2 sm:tw-grid-cols-1">
```

## Component Variants

```tsx
// ✅ Good - using cva for variants
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "tw-inline-flex tw-items-center tw-justify-center tw-rounded-md tw-text-sm tw-font-medium tw-transition-colors",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default:
          "tw-bg-primary tw-text-primary-foreground hover:tw-bg-primary/90",
        destructive:
          "tw-bg-destructive tw-text-destructive-foreground hover:tw-bg-destructive/90",
        outline:
          "tw-border tw-border-input tw-bg-background hover:tw-bg-accent",
      },
      size: {
        default: "tw-h-10 tw-px-4 tw-py-2",
        sm: "tw-h-9 tw-rounded-md tw-px-3",
        lg: "tw-h-11 tw-rounded-md tw-px-8",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
);
```

## Performance

- Use `@apply` sparingly, prefer utility classes
- Purge unused styles in production
- Use `tw-` prefix to avoid conflicts with other CSS
- Group related utilities with `@layer` when needed

## Accessibility

- Always include focus states
- Use semantic color tokens for better contrast
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Use `sr-only` for screen reader only content
